According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global ketchup market was valued at USD 3.21 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 3.85 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 2.7% during the forecast period. Market growth is being driven by increasing demand for convenience foods, the rapid expansion of quick-service restaurants (QSRs), rising consumption of fast food, and continuous product innovation focused on healthier and premium condiment offerings.
Ketchup remains one of the world's most widely consumed condiments, valued for its versatility across households, restaurants, and food processing industries. Primarily made from tomatoes, vinegar, sweeteners, and seasonings, it is widely used with burgers, fries, sandwiches, hot dogs, grilled meats, and snack products, while also serving as a base ingredient for sauces, marinades, and dressings.
